locality: Pinnacles Natl Monument, by Little Pinnacles
Harris Peak, N of Pinnacles National Monument

On Madrone Trail near intersection with Cathedral Rocks and Hidden Springs Trails. Population next to trail where gravel has eroded from upslope and piled at base. Evidence of significant pruning back of shrubs along trail. Common associates include Adenostoma fasciculatum, Ceanothus cuneatus var. cuneatus, Mimulus aurantiacus and Salvia mellifera. Aspect 150 degrees, slope approx 30 % and elevation 445 meters. N36.76442, W121.45000, NAD83. In Azalea Canyon Preserve within Hollister Hills State Vehicular Recreation Area.
